{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649347","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649347"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:03:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:03:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18361"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18361","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18361"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.04,0.04,0.24,0.56]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11079"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74368"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11079","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11079"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18361"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59859"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7472"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25695"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25698"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74368","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74368"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures is most lateral in the regional anatomy of the foot?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Tibialis anterior","Dorsalis pedis artery","Extensor hallucis longus","Deep fibular nerve","Extensor digitorum longus"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn the regional anatomy of the foot, the \u003Cstrong\u003Eextensor digitorum longus\u003C/strong\u003E is the most lateral structure among the options provided. It is located on the lateral side of the anterior compartment of the leg and extends into the foot, where it is positioned laterally compared to the other structures listed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etibialis anterior\u003C/strong\u003E is located medially in the anterior compartment of the leg and foot, making it more medial than the extensor digitorum longus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edorsalis pedis artery\u003C/strong\u003E runs along the dorsum of the foot, typically between the extensor hallucis longus and the extensor digitorum longus, but it is not the most lateral structure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eextensor hallucis longus\u003C/strong\u003E is positioned between the tibialis anterior and the extensor digitorum longus, making it more medial than the extensor digitorum longus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edeep fibular nerve\u003C/strong\u003E runs alongside the anterior tibial artery and is not the most lateral structure in the foot\u0027s anatomy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The extensor digitorum longus is the most lateral structure among the options provided in the context of the foot\u0027s regional anatomy.","Understanding the anatomical positioning of structures in the foot is crucial for clinical assessments and interventions."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of clinical and biochemical disorders of the skeleton. Oxford University Press","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Els